{"word":"φόβη","slug":"φόβη","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>φόβη</b></el> <el>(φόβη, ἡ,) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>a lock</i> or <i>curl of hair</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>the mane</i> of a horse, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a>, like <el>κόμη</el>, <i>the tresses</i> of trees, <i>foliage</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}